 Here we have to find multiples of 20 between 15 and 85.</think> <answer> $$15 \;{\color{red}\rightarrow} i=1; \;20*1=20 \;and \;20*1=20 \;is \;divisible \;by \;20 \\ {\color{black} {15 \;{\color{red} \nrightarrow} i=2} } 20*2=40 \;and \;20*2=40 \;is \;divisible \;by \;20}{\color{red} { } } \\ {\color{black} {15 \;{\color{red} \nrightarrow} i=3} } 20*3=60 \;and \;20*3=60 \;is \;divisible \;by \;20}} {\color{black} {15 \;{\color{red} \nrightarrow} i=4} }20*4=80 \;and \;80*4=80\; \;is \;divisible \;by \;20} \\ {\color{red} {85} \;{\color{red} \nrightarrow} i=5} 20*5=100 \;and \;100-85=15>0; \;i>0} \\ N=4$\end{eqnarray}{/eq}
Here we have to find multiples of 20 between 15 and 85.
i=1;20*1=20;(20*1=20 is divisible by 20)
i=2;20*2=40;(20*2=40 is divisible by 20);20*2=40;40*2=80;(80-40=40<0);
i=3;20*3=60;(20*3=60 is divisible by 20);20*3=60;60*2=120;120-60=60<0;
i=4;20*4=80;(20*4=80 is divisible by 20);20*4=80;80*2=140;140-80=60<0;
i=5;20*5=100;(100-85=15>0);
Therefore, the integers divisible by 20 between 15 and 85 are 20, 40, 60, and 80, making the total number 4.

