Four different dots can be chosen from 16 in $\binom{16}{4}$ ways. The maximum number of straight lines that can be traced from these four dots are 4. For any 4 collinear points chosen, they must lie on one line, and there are 5 different lines possible for a set of collinear dots. So, worded another way, 5 lines each with 4 dots, or 4 lines with 5 dots exist. </think>

